9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 410, L.D. 954, “An Act to Amend the
10 Law Governing the Membership of the Government Oversight Committee”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in the first indented paragraph in the 2nd, 3rd and 4th lines
12 (page 1, lines 15 to 17 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "Beginning with the 132nd
13 Legislature, at least one member of the committee must be a member of the joint standing
14 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over taxation matters" and inserting the
15 following: 'Beginning with the 132nd Legislature, at least one member of the committee
16 must be a member of the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
17 over taxation matters'
18 Amend the bill in section 1 in the first indented paragraph in the last line (page 1, line
19 20 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "party." and inserting the following: 'party.'
20 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
21 'Sec. 2. Retroactivity. This Act applies retroactively to December 4, 2024.'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment amends the bill by retaining the provision under current law that
2266 requires, beginning with the 132nd Legislature, at least one member of the Government
2277 Oversight Committee to be a member of the joint standing committee of the Legislature
2288 having jurisdiction over taxation matters. The amendment also amends the bill by adding
2299 a retroactivity clause to make this legislation apply retroactively to December 4, 2024.
